race.comment: DELICIOUS (2) showed little early speed at his last couple, the latest finishing fifth (30.82) in a Grade 5 at The Meadows. Key runner on his best form. DR. YELLOWSTONE (3) has missed the placings at his last couple but was in the money three back when third (28.33) at Bendigo in a Grade 5 H. Key player on best and worth another try. MR. PRESIDENT (1) produced a modest effort most recently when fifth at Shepparton over 450m behind Typhoon Baylee (25.57) in a Grade 4/5. Comes through a solid form race last start. Leading chance. BRINDLE SURPRISE (8) is not to be discarded. Something for the Multiples: JOEY (6)
